-- Witness Patrol — per-rig worker monitor patrol loop.
-- Pit Boss: watch polecats, nudge toward completion, verify state, escalate.

## witness-patrol

  input param.wisp_type : str default("patrol")

  # inbox-check : llm
    system>
      You are the Witness processing patrol mail.
      Clean up your own wisps first (swim lane rule: never close foreign wisps).
      Drain stale protocol messages, then process inbox by type.
    user>
      ```bash
      bd mol wisp gc --closed --force
      bd mol wisp gc --age 1h --force
      gt mail drain --identity <rig>/witness --max-age 30m
      gt mail inbox
      ```
      If >10 messages: batch by type (POLECAT_DONE, MERGED, HELP).
      POLECAT_STARTED: acknowledge, archive.
      POLECAT_DONE: persistent model — polecat goes idle, not nuked.
      If pending MR: create cleanup wisp + MERGE_READY to refinery.
      If no MR: acknowledge idle. Archive.
      MERGED: close cleanup wisp if exists. Do NOT nuke polecat. Archive.
      HELP: classify, resolve or escalate, archive.
      HANDOFF: absorb context, archive.
      SWARM_START: create swarm tracking wisp, archive.
    accept>
      Inbox processed, messages archived.
  #/

  # process-cleanups : llm
    - inbox-check
    system>
      You are processing cleanup wisps (merge tracking and dirty state).
    user>
      ```bash
      bd list --label cleanup --status=open
      ```
      If none, skip.
      For each: extract polecat name, diagnose problem:
      ```bash
      cd polecats/<name>
      git status --porcelain
      git stash list
      git log @{u}..HEAD
      ```
      Uncommitted: commit and push. Stashed: pop or discard.
      Unpushed: push to origin. Then restart session.
      If unresolvable: escalate to Deacon with RECOVERY_NEEDED.
    accept>
      All cleanup wisps resolved or escalated.
  #/

  # check-refinery : llm
    - process-cleanups
    system>
      You are checking refinery and deacon health.
    user>
      Check refinery:
      ```bash
      gt session status <rig>/refinery
      ```
      If MRs waiting and refinery not running:
      ```bash
      gt session start <rig>/refinery
      gt mail send <rig>/refinery -s "PATROL: Wake up" -m "MRs in queue."
      gt mol step emit-event --channel refinery --type PATROL_WAKE \
        --payload source=witness --payload queue_depth=<N>
      ```
      Queue health:
      ```bash
      gt refinery ready --all --json
      ```
      Look for: stale claimed MRs, orphaned branches, queue depth.
      Check deacon:
      ```bash
      tmux has-session -t hq-deacon 2>/dev/null && echo "alive" || echo "dead"
      ```
      If dead: escalate to Mayor.
    format> health
      { refinery: str, deacon: str, queue_depth: number, stale_mrs: number }
  #/

  # survey-workers : llm
    - check-refinery
    system>
      You are surveying all polecats via agent beads and tmux cross-reference.
      Primary: discover completions from agent bead metadata.
      Critical: zombie detection (dead session + running state).
      Swim lane: only close wisps YOU created.
    user>
      Step 0 - Discover completions from beads (exit_type + completion_time).
      Step 1 - List polecat agent beads:
      ```bash
      bd list --type=agent --json
      ```
      Step 2 - For each polecat, check agent_state.
      Running/working: zombie detect via tmux:
      ```bash
      gt session status <rig>/<name> --json | jq -r '.running'
      ```
      Zombie (dead session, says running): check hook_bead status first.
      If hook_bead closed: just restart session (work done, expected).
      If dirty: escalate RECOVERY_NEEDED to Deacon.
      Spawning: check spawn age. >10 min = stale, escalate.
      Idle: leave alone (sandbox preserved). Check for pending MR.
      Step 3 - Assess progress for live sessions:
      ```bash
      gt peek <rig>/<name> 20
      ```
      Step 5 - Execute nudges:
      ```bash
      gt nudge --mode=queue <rig>/polecats/<name> "How's progress?"
      ```
      Step 7 - Orphaned bead detection:
      ```bash
      bd list --status=in_progress --json --limit=0
      bd list --status=hooked --json --limit=0
      ```
      If session dead AND directory missing: reset bead, notify Deacon.
    format> survey
      { total: number, alive: number, zombies: number, idle: number, nudged: number }
  #/

  # check-timer-gates : script
    - survey-workers
    ```bash
    bd gate check --type=timer --escalate 2>&1
    echo "timer_gates_checked"
    ```

    ```oracle
    assert output contains "timer_gates_checked";
    ```
  #/

  # check-swarm-completion : llm
    - check-timer-gates
    system>
      You are checking if an active swarm batch is complete.
    user>
      ```bash
      bd list --label swarm --status=open
      ```
      If no active swarm, skip.
      Count completed polecats for this swarm.
      If all complete:
      ```bash
      gt mail send mayor/ -s "SWARM_COMPLETE: <swarm_id>" -m "All <N> polecats merged."
      bd close <swarm-wisp-id> --reason "All polecats merged"
      ```
    accept>
      Swarm status checked.
  #/

  # patrol-cleanup : llm
    - check-swarm-completion
    system>
      You are cleaning up inbox at end of patrol cycle.
    user>
      ```bash
      gt mail drain --identity <rig>/witness --max-age 30m
      gt mail inbox
      ```
      Archive stale processed messages.
      Check cleanup wisp hygiene:
      ```bash
      bd list --label cleanup --status=open
      ```
      Goal: inbox nearly empty, cleanup wisps rare.
    accept>
      Inbox clean.
  #/

  # context-check : decision
    - patrol-cleanup
    system>
      You are checking your own context usage.
    user>
      If context HIGH (>80%): prepare for handoff.
      If context LOW: can continue patrolling.
    format> verdict
      { context: str, action: str }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.action in ["CONTINUE", "HANDOFF"];
    ```
  #/

  # loop-or-exit : script
    - context-check
    ```bash
    if [ "{{context-check.action}}" = "HANDOFF" ]; then
      gt handoff -s "Witness patrol handoff" -m "Context high, cycling."
      echo "action=HANDOFF"
    else
      gt mol step await-signal --agent-bead YOUR_AGENT_BEAD \
        --backoff-base 30s --backoff-mult 2 --backoff-max 5m
      gt patrol report --summary "Patrol cycle complete."
      echo "action=LOOP"
    fi
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: patrol include_metrics: true

##/
